---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';
import BlogCrossLinks from '../../components/BlogCrossLinks.astro';

const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<Layout title="How Tall is 6 Feet in Centimeters? Height Reference" description="How tall is 6 feet in cm? Exactly 182.88 cm. Height comparisons and context for this common benchmark." keywords="6 feet in cm, 6 foot height, 182 cm in feet, how tall is 6 feet, height comparison, 6ft centimeters, tall height reference">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-600">Blog</a> <span class="mx-1">›</span> <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Length</span>
      </nav>
      <BlogCrossLinks title="How Tall is 6 Feet in Centimeters? Height Reference" />
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">June 17, 2025 • 3 min read</p>

      <p>Six feet is one of the most frequently referenced heights in English-speaking countries. But if you grew up with the metric system, what does that actually look like? Here is the definitive answer plus context.</p>

      <h2>The Exact Conversion</h2>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl p-5 my-6 not-prose">
        <p class="text-center text-lg font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">6 feet = 182.88 cm = 1.8288 m</p>
        <p class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">6 feet = 72 inches (each foot = 12 inches, each inch = 2.54 cm)</p>
      </div>

      <h2>Heights Around 6 Feet</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>5'10" = 177.8 cm (1.78 m)</li>
        <li>5'11" = 180.3 cm (1.80 m)</li>
        <li>6'0" = 182.9 cm (1.83 m)</li>
        <li>6'1" = 185.4 cm (1.85 m)</li>
        <li>6'2" = 188.0 cm (1.88 m)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Is 6 Feet Tall?</h2>
      <p>It depends on where you are. Globally, 6 feet (183 cm) is well above average for men and significantly above average for women:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>World average (men):</strong> 171 cm (5'7") — so 6 feet is 12 cm above average</li>
        <li><strong>USA average (men):</strong> 175.4 cm (5'9")</li>
        <li><strong>Netherlands average (men):</strong> 183.8 cm (6'0") — one of the tallest countries</li>
        <li><strong>World average (women):</strong> 159 cm (5'3")</li>
      </ul>
      <p>In the US, roughly 14.5% of men are 6 feet or taller. In countries like the Netherlands or Montenegro, it is closer to average.</p>

      <h2>Quick Mental Conversions for Heights Near 6 Feet</h2>
      <p>A useful anchor: 180 cm is very close to 5'11" (just 3 mm off). So if someone says they are 180 cm, they are essentially 5'11". Add 2.5 cm for each additional inch:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>180 cm = 5'11"</li>
        <li>183 cm = 6'0"</li>
        <li>185 cm = 6'1"</li>
        <li>188 cm = 6'2"</li>
        <li>190 cm = 6'3"</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Fun Facts About 6 Feet</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Most airplane overhead bins are about 6 feet off the ground</li>
        <li>Standard interior door frames are 6'8" (203 cm)</li>
        <li>A standard bathtub is 5 feet — a 6-footer will not fit flat</li>
        <li>The term "six-footer" has been used in English since the 1830s</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mt-10 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Try It Now</h3>
        <a href="/convert/length" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 text-white text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-amber-600 transition-colors">Open Length Converter →</a>
      </div>
    
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 p-4 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium">🔗 Try our converter: <a href="/convert/length" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 font-bold hover:underline">Open Converter →</a></p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
